  "prompt": "What are substitutes for parsnips in recipes?",
  "response": "If you need substitutes for parsnips in recipes, here are several options you can consider:\n\n1. **Carrots**: They have a similar texture and sweetness, though they are less starchy.\n2. **Sweet Potatoes**: These offer a sweeter flavor and a creamy texture when cooked.\n3. **Turnips**: They have a slightly peppery taste and can mimic the texture of parsnips.\n4. **Rutabaga**: This has a sweet, earthy flavor and is a good substitute in soups and stews.\n5. **Celeriac (Celery Root)**: It has a similar starchy texture and a mild flavor that works well in many dishes.\n6. **Potatoes**: Regular potatoes can be used, though they will alter the flavor and texture.\n7. **Beets**: While they have a different flavor, roasted or cooked beets can add a unique twist to a dish.\n8. **Butternut Squash**: Provides sweetness and a creamy texture, especially in soups.\n\nWhen substituting, consider the dish's flavor profile and how the texture of the substitute will work with the other ingredients.",
